  "doc_id": "5541",
  "text": "The very high sensitivity of the presented sensor comes from the structure of the supramolecular complex of HSCX-COOH-DA, formed at the gold electrode surface, as a consequence of the intermolecular recognition process. This complex is formed by means of electrostatic interaction between the dissociated carboxylic group of host molecules and protonated amino group of guest molecules. Additionally, the nitrogen from the piperidine ring creates the hydrogen bond with the hydroxyl group of DA. As a result, the DA is located outside of the macrocyclic cavity ( Figure S2 ). Such localization of DA facilitates the run of its redox reaction and, consequently, the strong analytical signal is generated. This work Au-gold electrode; Cys-cysteamine; Dopa_RNA aptamer-the RNA aptamer for dopamine; CV-cyclic voltammetry; CA-chronoamprometry; CH-catechol; NEP-norepinephrine; EP-epinephrine; L-DOPA-3,4-dihydroxy-phenylalanine; DOPAC-3,4-dihydroxyphenylacetic acid; Tyr-tyramine; HMP-methyldopamine; HS-Dopa_RNA aptamer-the 57-mer 5'-thiol-C6-modified RNA aptamer specific for dopamine; PEI membrane-polyetyleneimine membrane; CACE-calix [CITATION_1] arene crown-4 ether; DPV-differential pulse voltammetry; AA-ascorbic acid; UA-uric acid; TC8A-thiolated calix [CITATION_2] arene; TC6A-thiolated calix [CITATION_3] arene; TC4A-thiolated calix [CITATION_4] arene; GCE-glassy carbon electrode; CUCR-C-Undecylcalix [CITATION_5] resorcinarene; LB-Langmuir-Blodgett; C4A-calix [CITATION_6] resorcinarene; RGO-reduced graphen oxide; P5A-pillar [CITATION_7] arene; MET-2-mercaptoethanol; HSCX-COOH-5,17-Bis[N-(4-carboxypiperidino)methyl]-25,27-bis(3-mercaptopropoxy)-26,28-dihydroxycalix [CITATION_8] arene; SWV-square-wave voltammetry.",
